{"serial": "22011", "department_serial": 21, "code": "PH1028", "class": "B", "name": {"en": "Electromagnetism", "ch": "電磁學"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Cheng, Wang-Yau"], "ch": ["鄭王曜"]}, "credits": 4, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 1, "session": ["3", "4"]}, "loc": {"building": "S4", "room": "202"}}, {"time": {"week": 3, "session": ["1", "2"]}, "loc": {"building": "S4", "room": "202"}}], "isRequired": true, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": -1, "department": {"ch": "物理學系", "en": "Department of Physics"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "全部使用", "en": "All"}, "assigned": 0, "selected": 28, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "電磁學有兩樣特徵：1. 物理定律非常多; 2.數學的依賴度非常高 (主要為向量分析)。如何讓學生，在沒有學過普通物理的情形下，不至於成為”見樹(電磁定律)而不見林(馬克斯威爾方程與相對論)”的漂鳥", "en": "Electromagnetism has two characteristics: 1. There are many physical laws; 2. It relies heavily on mathematics (mainly vector analysis). How to prevent students who have not learned general physics from becoming a stry bird of  “seeing the trees (the laws of electromagnetism) but not the forest (Maxwell’s equations and theory of relativity)”"}, "outline": {"ch": "預計本學期的課程大綱(視學習狀況)：\n先見林(期中考以前)，再見樹(期中考以後)\n1.古典力學觀念的複習，包含球座標積分，偏微分與梯度等這門課常用到的數學。\n2.簡介真空Maxwell equations (積分式)與其實驗背景。這部份以普物課本為主。\n3.真空中”一點”的電磁場所需要遵循的Maxwell eqs.如何用數學表達？從 ”點” 場源到 ”連續分布” 的場源 (引入梯度，旋度等數學工具。)\n4.電磁波的形成與光速\n5.期中考(筆記與口試)\n6.電位與向量位的制定\n7.邊界條件的重要性\n8.電場如果不是在真空，Maxwell eqs如何修改(1)？\n甲、金屬與介電值\n乙、電偶極與折射率\n丙、不同介質的邊界條件\n9.磁場如果不是在真空，Maxwell eqs如何修改(2)？\n甲、金屬與介電值\n乙、磁偶極與折射率\n丙、不同介質的邊界條件\n10.電磁場隨時間變化、電磁能量與動量與poynting vector\n11.再寫一遍Maxwell eqs\n甲、在介質中\n乙、庫倫規範與勞倫茲規範\n12.Maxwell的時代為什麼有人不信會有電磁波？\n13.*四向量與張量與勞倫茲轉換\n14.*淺談相對論", "en": "Estimated course syllabus for this semester (depending on study status of students):\n1. Review of classical mechanics concepts, including spherical coordinate integrals, partial differentials and gradients and other mathematics commonly used in this course.\n2. Introduction to vacuum Maxwell equations (integral equations) and its experimental background. This part is mainly based on general physics textbooks.\n3. The electromagnetic field at a “point“ in vacuum needs to follow the Maxwell eqs. How to express it mathematically? From “point“ field source to “continuous distribution“ field source (introducing mathematical tools such as gradient and curl.)\n4. The formation of electromagnetic waves and the speed of light\n5. Midterm exam (notes and oral exam)\n6. Formulation of potential and vector potential\n7. Importance of boundary conditions\n8. If the electric field is not in a vacuum, how to modify Maxwell eqs (1)?\nA. Metal and dielectric value\nB. Electric dipole and refractive index\nC. Boundary conditions of different media\n9. If the magnetic field is not in a vacuum, how to modify Maxwell eqs (2)?\nA. Metal and dielectric value\nB. Magnetic dipole and refractive index\nC. Boundary conditions of different media\n10. Changes of electromagnetic field with time, electromagnetic energy and momentum and poynting vector\n11. Write Maxwell eqs again\nA. In the medium\nB. Coulomb norm and Lorenz norm\n12. Why didn’t some people believe in electromagnetic waves in Maxwell’s time?\n13. *Four vectors and tensors and Lorenz transformation\n14. *A brief discussion on the theory of relativity"}, "textbook": {"ch": "David Griffiths著 , Introduction to electrodynamics, Person出版，第3版或第五版好處︰非常普及的教科書﹐考研或重修兩相宜\n\nHarris Benson, University Physics, third revised edition\n好處︰非常普及的教科書﹐版本的變化不大﹐圖書館有﹐容易借得到或買得到二手書本。(我去年教光電及生醫﹐所用的課本)", "en": "1. David Griffiths , Introduction to electrodynamics, Person publisher, third or fifth edition.\n\n2. Harris Benson, University Physics, third revised edition"}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "40%", "en": "40%"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授", "en": ["Lecture"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "加分：全勤與上課態度︰最多8 ％\n(你不及格時才會考慮這部份，及格同學完全無關) \n期中考︰50 ％\n期末考︰50 ％\n加分：平時考：10％\n學期總成績最高分99分。作弊學期成績零分。", "en": "Bonus points: perfect attendance and attitude in class: up to 8％\n(This part will only be considered if you fail, this bonus has nothing to do with the students who passed)\nMidterm exam: 50％\nFinal exam: 50％\nExtra points: Normal test: 10％\nThe maximum total score for the semester is 99 points. The semester grade for cheating will be zero."}, "officeHour": {"ch": "當學生連絡我時", "en": "at the time as students contact me"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "16+2", "en": "16+2"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "由於這課程是針對未修過普通物理的同學﹐因此保留兩週的彈性以便視同學吸收的狀況而定", "en": "Since this course is aimed at students who have not taken general physics, the flexibility of two weeks is reserved to allow students to take advantage of the situation."}, "domain": {"ch": "原子與分子物理\n\n\n、\n\n\n電漿與強場光學", "en": "原子與分子物理\n\n\n、\n\n\n電漿與強場光學"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "基礎物理", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習", "口頭報告/口試"]}, {"competencies": "進階物理", "rating": "(3)普通", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習", "口頭報告/口試"]}, {"competencies": "邏輯分析與獨立思考", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習", "口頭報告/口試"]}, {"competencies": "團隊經營", "rating": "(1)非常低", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習", "口頭報告/口試"]}, {"competencies": "自我學習能力", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習", "口頭報告/口試"]}, {"competencies": "語文與論述能力", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習", "口頭報告/口試"]}, {"competencies": "實驗能力", "rating": "(2)低", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習", "口頭報告/口試"]}, {"competencies": "電腦應用與程式設計", "rating": "(2)低", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習", "口頭報告/口試"]}, {"competencies": "專題計畫執行", "rating": "(3)普通", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習", "口頭報告/口試"]}, {"competencies": "學術倫理", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習", "口頭報告/口試"]}], "en": [{"competencies": "Elementary physics", "rating": "(5)VeryHigh", "assesments": ["Test/Exam", "Assignments", "Presentation/Oral Exam"]}, {"competencies": "Intermediate physics", "rating": "(3)Medium", "assesments": ["Test/Exam", "Assignments", "P